n february  the company announced that it had acquired the private client division of newton management limited a uk wealth management unit of bny mellon in a deal worth up to £ million in march  it was announced that standard life was in advanced talks to purchase rival phoenix group holdings’ ignis asset management for around £ million towards the end of the month standard life completed the acquisition for a fee of £ million in september  standard life agreed to sell its canadian operations to the manufacturers life insurance company a subsidiary of manulife financial corporation it completed this sale on  january  for a cash consideration of cbn the transaction included a global collaboration agreement where manulife will seek to distribute standard life investments funds in canada the us and asia in a roundup of  business pretax profits rose by  to £m feebased revenue during the year grew  to bn and over  autoenrolment customers were added the pay and bonus of chief executive david nish rose by  to almost £m in february  standard life announced it was launching a wholly owned ukwide financial advice business saying it was “responding to fundamental changes that were driving unprecedented demand for advice from customers” in doing so it confirmed that it had entered into an agreement with skipton building society to purchase pearson jones a firm of financial advisers and paraplanners and this acquisition was completed in may  when the name of its new financial advice business was announced as “” – a reference to the year standard life was founded in july  a property investment fund managed by standard life investments froze withdrawals after experiencing liquidity issues in march  standard life reached an agreement to merge with aberdeen asset management in an allshare merger subject to shareholder approval operationsedit standard life is an investment company headquartered in edinburgh with operations across the globe it employs around  people internationally through businesses in the uk europe north america asia and australasia it has around  million customers and clients across  countries and is responsible for the administration of over £bn of their assets the company has a further  million customers through its indian and chinese associate and joint venture businesses  hdfc life in india and heng an standard life in china in the uk standard life also owns three subsidiary businesses focus solutions a software and consultancy business threesixty a services provider and vebnet a software and services provider standard life has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and has around  million individual shareholders it is also listed in a number of the dow jones sustainability indices djsi including the djsi world which ranks the worlds leading sustainabilitydriven publicly listed companies senior managementedit the company’s board of directors is made up of a chairman four executive directors and seven nonexecutive directors the board has nine men and three women details of the chairman and executive directors include sir gerry grimstone chairman appointed in may  keith skeoch chief executive appointed on  august  replacing david nish luke savage chief financial officer appointed in august  colin clark director global client group appointed in november  barry odwyer ceo pensions and savings appointed in march  the nonexecutive directors are pierre danon appointed in october  noel harwerth appointed in july  lynne peacock appointed in april  martin pike appointed in september  kevin parry appointed in october  melanie gee appointed in november  john devine appointed in july  controversyedit in january  standard life were accused of smearing a policyholder michael hogan who was not happy with the way the company was being run an email sent to standard life executives and advisors which was disclosed under the data protection act revealed an attempt to discredit him in january  the head of standard lifes life and pensions business trevor matthews used the racist phrase nigger in the woodpile while giving a presentation at one of the companys edinburgh offices after issuing an apology mr matthews remained in his job and no disciplinary action was taken in march  the company announced it would cut  jobs in an attempt to save an additional £ million per year in costs one month later it was highlighted in the companys annual report that three of standard lifes top executives sandy crombie keith skeoch and trevor matthews were awarded more than £ million in pay a standard life spokesman defended the awards citing the leaderships efforts in turning round the companys fortunes in february  standard life announced that it may move parts of their operations outside scotland in the event of scottish independence if it was necessary to do so referencesedit  a b c annual report  pdf retrieved  april    a b c about standard life standardlifecom retrieved  april    london stock exchange market news retrieved  february    a b standard life history one of the first empire builders the scotsman  september   standard life policyholders rush to cash in on flotation the guardian  september   barclays buys standard life bank for £m daily telegraph  october   standard life takes full control of threesixty the scotsman  march   standard life sells healthcare division bbc news  may   standard life buys focus for £m bbc news  december   nicole blackmore  february  standard life wealth acquires newtons private client division fundweb   richa naidu  march  standard life in advanced talks to buy phoenix asset management unit reuters   simon jessop  march  standard life ramps up fund business with ignis acquisition reuters   manulife to buy standard lifes canadian assets for  billion reuters  september   cityam news  disposal of canadian companies cityam retrieved  february    bbc news  standard life reports sharp rise in operating profit bbc news retrieved  march    london stock exchange market news london